                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230625-35-off211 t18230625-35-crimeloc215"></join>. On the 6th of June, about half past three o'clock in the afternoon, I was coming out of the back room, and saw the prisoner reaching across the counter, with his hand in the till; he ran out; I followed him, and called Stop thief! he was stopped in my sight. Thirteen shillings and a halfpenny was brought to me. I missed silver from the till, but cannot say how much.</p>
