            . I am a baker, and live in Marylebone. I saw the prisoner running in Baker-street, and people following him; he ran behind a carriage, took something from his pocket, and put it behind the carriage wheel. I went there and picked up nine shillings, eight sixpences and a halfpenny, which I gave to Brooks. He was stopped directly.</p>
